      • binarySearch

        public static <E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>> int binarySearch(E[] array,
                                                                   E target)
        Binary search method that works with generics.
        NOTE: All arrays must be pre-sorted. Extra private method including low and high index limits is also required for recursive implementation.
        Type Parameters:
        E - Objects in the array MUST implement Comparable interface.
        Parameters:
        array - The array to be searched through.
        target - The value to search the array for.
        Returns:
        Returns call to binarySearch that includes extra parameters.
